Hi,

`Node2D` has `get_pos` and `get_global_pos` to get position relative to the parent node or global to the scene.
On the other hand it seems it only have `get_rot`, so why not add a `get_global_rot` ?

Beside it implementation would be pretty similar to `get_global_pos`:

``` cpp
float Node2D::get_global_rot() const {

    return get_global_transform().get_rotation();
}
```

I can submit a PR if you're interested ;-)
